      "date": "2026-04-13",
      "applied_by": "celeste-cli v1.9.0 feat/v1.9-quality-bundle",
      "description": "Removed \"query\" from stop_words.typescript. The celeste-stopwords v1.0.0 artifact classified \"query\" as ubiquitous noise in the TS corpus (it IS high-DF via prisma), but celeste-cli applies the stop-word filter symmetrically at index time (per-language) and query time (universal only). That asymmetry breaks Q3 \"database connection pool query\" on TypeScript codebases because MySQLQuery and similar types lose their \"query\" token from their shingle sets while the query keeps it. celeste-stopwords should add \"query\" to the -preserve flag default in cmd/derive for v1.0.1."
    }
  ]
